BACKGROUND: Everybody likes CS_OFFICE, and I thought that for the FUN of EVERYONE... It would be cool to give a new look to this great map... I heard on servers that everybody was a bit tired of the legendary "plaster/offwllc" so I hope you will enjoy the "renovations" (sorry i'm french). But Anyway had very poor fps and an endless time of compiling. I promise people try yourself to use a vmex vmf of a css original map and you'll see the crap result . I have to play The DOCTOR lol to have something can start begin to work with. Lights.. props .. the skybox etc ( the skybox was a road to hell) ... AT first try I had very low fps... NOw ... The Map is Really FAST ! and my PC is prehistorical ^^ - Ambiance I really tried my best not to modify cs_office the wrong way guys :( . as you can see i did 'nt try to build some kind of new stupid ways into the map ! I JUST tried to make something that will look a little bit more " A LA MODE " like we are saying in france lol ! About the outside places . The lights are bright enough so you can see the enemy. no problem ^^ - Materials Hope you will like my "redluxwood" texture The wood is a bit shiny and luxious. The black board texture. Well, here it is, after around 2 months of development from the origional idea, I bring you cs_office2.

My main objective was to create a sequal to the map cs_office, trying to stay with the origional style as closley as possible and creating a whole new map that plays completlyy differently.

This map has 40 player spawn points, has the radar overview images and has HDR lighting to finish it off.  Decent frames throughout the whole map, even when running bots.

Finally, I hope you all enjoy playing it!

This map has been re-uploaded and should now work Installation: You should have no trouble extracting the contents of the zip to your cstrike folder. (eg steamapps\your-email\counter-strike source\cstrike) Failing that use the folder structure in the zip to see where the files need to go. Map Details: cs_office07 is a 100% re-make of Turtle Rock's cs_office, no copy and pasting - map was built from scratch brush by brush. Author: Simon 'Blink' Smith
You can contact me via this form regarding anything about this map.

Of course credit given to original map designers and source version mappers.

Map is basically the same layout as original office when there are 16 or less players spawned.

When the map counts more than 16 players at spawn, the map will open its doors to all of the extended areas.

For testing purposes, you can run the map and add enough bots to trigger the extension.

You will know when the map is extended or not by a message which is displayed in the players hud at spawn.

The reason I made the map this way is because its just too big for a few players to join and get it started, players can join, have fun in the near-normal cs_office layout then once the server players grow, they can have more space to play.

***Note***
I have put up a newer version with a few minor fixes to some bugs that came to my attention after putting the map up. Re-download after the "last modified" time to get the best version. Thanks.

Title: cs_occupation
Version: release 1.0
Spawnpoints: 64
Map Type: Hostage Rescue
Author: Emil Fridell
Alias: Pingu
Email address: emil.fridell@spray.se

====================================================
Background:

Terrorists have taken hostage at an office. Counter-terrorists have
arrived and are ready to begin there assault.


Mission Briefing:

Counter-terrorist: Rescue the hostage or eliminate all terrorists

Terrorist:  Prevent the CT from rescue the hostages.

====================================================

Oasthouse - Hostage Rescue

Description: Terrorists have taken 4 hostages in an abandoned oasthouse in Kent, England.  The British SAS have set up in a nearby barn poised to strike.

Counter-Terrorist Objective: Rescue the hostages from the abandoned oasthouse and return them to the barn.  Use the tunnel for a stealth strategy but be aware of ambushes, or rush through the allotment quickly.  The Courtyard is vulnerable to snipers but has lots of connective strategy. 

Terrorist Objective: Prevent Counter-Terrorists from rescuing the hostages. Use the upper floor for sniping terrorists in the courtyard. Terrorists can reach the greenhouse first. Guard the hostages using the house as cover.

Note: There is a switch to operate the garage door for an alternative exit.
The README file is inside the RAR.

DESCRIPTION:

****NEW YORK SIEGE****
ONCE AGAIN the phoenix terrorist cell has taken control of the DSB Computer Solutions building in downtown New York, only this time its in the middle of a ferocious New York blizzard. In considerably similar circumstances,the terrorists have taken four DSB employees hostage in the second conference room situated in the south building. 

Terrorists: Prevent the oncoming counter-terrorist assault by all means necessary; do not let the hostages escape.

Counter-Terrorists: Rescue all 4 hostages and take out all enemies. Proceed with extreme caution.



*******CONTACT INFO******** 
If you have any problems please contact me on msn at happyapple_42@hotmail.com
Be sure to visit the New York site for information on future mapping projects.

YOU MAY upload to any website, SO LONG as full credit is given AND that I am notified through the above email address. Thank You.
